In 2010, the population of the Summerhaven census-designated place was 40.<ref name="Census 2010"/> Note that this includes only people who were living in Summerhaven on the day of the census, thus excluding many part-time or seasonal residents. As of the 2010 census, the racial composition of Summerhaven was:

* [[White American|White]]: 75% ([[Non-Hispanic Whites]]: 70%)
* [[African American|Black or African American]]: 0%
* [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]]: 15%
* [[Asian American|Asian]]: 10%
* [[Pacific Islander American|Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander]]: 0%
* Some other race: 0%
* [[Multiracial American|Two or more races]]: 0%<ref>{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US0470175| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1): Summerhaven CDP, Arizona| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau| work=American Factfinder| access-date=January 27, 2016| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213115126/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US0470175| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>

